HEADWORD: Queest
<hw>Queest</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Icel.
<ets>kvisa</ets> a kind of bird, <ets>kvistr</ets> a branch of a tree,
and E. <ets>cushat</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The European
ringdove (<spn>Columba palumbus</spn>); the cushat.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>quist</asp>, <asp>queeze</asp>,
<asp>quice</asp>, <asp>queece</asp>.]</altsp> See <er>Ringdove</er>.⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

